<div class="leftblock">

	<h2>Envirochem has been in business since 1989, offering a wide range of analytical and consultancy services at the standard expected by our UKAS accreditation and various certifications. Our analytical staff have a wealth of knowledge and well over 100 years of combined surveying experience behind them</h2>
     
	<h1>Who are we?</h1>
	<p>Envirochem offer reliability and efficiency through the collaboration of more than 50 full-time members of staff including consultants, project managers, chemists, analysts, surveyors and laboratory technicians each holding <a href="http://www.bohs.org/" target="_blank">British Occupational Hygiene Society</a> (BOHS) certification applicable to their role and mobile laboratories to enable on-site analysis.</p>
	<p>Our <a href="?p=branches&amp;t=hampshire">head office</a>, managed by seasoned experts of the asbestos industry with the help of a growing administrative team, is located in the town of Fareham, Hampshire on the south coast of England. We are positioned between two major cities and work very hard to meet the needs of all of our clients, and maintain a fast turn around as required by the industry.</p>
	<p>We also have a <a href="?p=branches&amp;t=bristol">regional branch</a> in the city of Bristol, within the south-west of England. This recent development has enabled us to expand into new regions, improve our efficiently, spread our workload and reduce our call out times.</p>

	<h1>Why choose Envirochem?</h1>
    <p>We are accredited by the <a href="http://www.ukas.com/technical-information/technical-committee/absestos-tac/Asbestos-TAC.asp" target="_blank">United Kingdom Accreditation Service</a> (UKAS) for various <a href="?p=asbestos">asbestos testing, inspection</a> and <a href="?p=chemicals">chemical analysis</a> services, which are carried out in accordance with in-house procedures based upon guidance from the <a href="http://www.hse.gov.uk/asbestos/" target="_blank">Health and Safety Executive</a> (HSE).</p>
    <p>We are also accredited to <a href="http://www.mcerts.uk.com/index/" target="_blank">MCERTS</a> by the <a href="http://www.environment-agency.gov.uk/" target="_blank">Environment Agency</a> for <a href="?p=chemicals&amp;t=soil-analysis/">soil analysis</a>, and hold a license from the HSE to <a href="?p=asbestos&amp;t=removal-supervision">supervise and manage asbestos removal projects</a>.</p>
    <p>Additionally we are members of, and hold certification from various organisations including the <a href="http://www.chas.gov.uk" target="_blank">Contractors Health and Safety Assessment</a> (CHAS) scheme for our standard of health and safety and <a href="http://www.constructionline.co.uk/static/about-us.html" target="_blank">Constructionline</a> as a pre-qualified contractor.</p>
    <p>It is important to note that Envirochem is a solely independent organisation not affiliated with any other company. We offer a personal approach to all of our clients and guarantee unbiased, impartial and accurate information and results at all times.</p>

